# Constants Pattern

## Strings
- All user-facing text (labels, headers, tab names, help descriptions, button text, error messages, status labels) must be defined in `internal/constants/strings.go`
- Never hardcode display strings in view or component files
- Use descriptive constant names: `TabFeatures`, `HelpDescViewJourney`, `ButtonViewInBrowser`

## Config & Paths
- File names, URLs, package specs, and directory names go in `internal/constants/constants.go`
- Output file names: `FeatureRegistryFile = "feature-registry.json"`, etc.

## Example

```go
// constants/strings.go
const TabFeatures = "Features"

// views/results.go — use the constant
tabs: []string{constants.TabFeatures, constants.TabGrowthManifest}
```
